OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1779991869
OL,3,CBirmingham City Council pays itself
OL,4,Calmost #500,000 in charges and fines
OL,6,FAlthough the authority has faced a
OL,7,Fcontinuous bin strike since January
OL,8,F2025, most of the vehicles which drew
OL,9,Fdaily charges were from its waste
OL,10,Fdepartment.
OL,12,FThe council says it has been replacing
OL,13,Fnon-compliant vehicles over the past
OL,14,F12 months and wants "eco driving"
OL,15,Facross its fleet.
OL,17,FHowever, it admitted that 142 (12%) of
OL,18,Fthe 1,170 vehicles in its fleet, as of
OL,19,F31 March, remained non-compliant with
OL,20,Fthe CAZ requirements (which have been
OL,21,Fin place since 2021).
OL,26,@vD@UOUvD@aO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/6
